            <head>Biographical Note</head>

            <p>Elizabeth Jane Miller, 1878-1961, was born near New Ross, Indiana. In 1908 she married Oren Stephen Hack, an Indianapolis attorney who died in 1942. Her four published novels were <title render="italic">The Yoke</title> in 1904, <title render="italic">Saul of Tarsus</title> in 1906, <title render="italic">The City of Delight</title> in 1908, and <title render="italic">Daybreak</title> in 1915, all issued under her maiden name.</p>

        </bioghist>
        
